  "body": "Since #1425, when doing a `make` while in a branch (not master), the build fails in the `godeps` target.  This is also the cause of the `coredns/ci` integration test failures.\r\n\r\n```\r\ngo get -u github.com/coredns/forward\r\n# cd /Users/cohaver/go/src/github.com/coredns/coredns; git pull --ff-only\r\nThere is no tracking information for the current branch.\r\nPlease specify which branch you want to merge with.\r\nSee git-pull(1) for details.\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\nManually doing `go get -v -u github.com/coredns/forward` yields ...\r\n\r\n```\r\ngo get -v -u github.com/coredns/forward\r\ngithub.com/coredns/forward (download)\r\ngithub.com/coredns/coredns (download)\r\n# cd /Users/cohaver/go/src/github.com/coredns/coredns; git pull --ff-only\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo - git appears to be getting confused when trying to get coredns, which happens to be the current repository.",
